{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID` is exposed as an env var ONLY in the remote/cloud runner; the LOCAL\nClaude Code CLI does not export it. Without a shim the session-provenance feature silently\nno-ops for local-CLI users â€” the most common case. The robust, harness-agnostic capture is a\nClaude Code SessionStart hook that reads the hook's `session_id` from stdin and exports it as\nthe portable `REBAR_SESSION_ID`, plus the harness tag `AI_AGENT=claude-code`.\n\n## What\n- **Hook script (`scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh`).** Reads the\n  SessionStart JSON envelope from stdin (field `session_id`) and, when `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is\n  set, APPENDS `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=<id>` and `export AI_AGENT=claude-code` to it (the\n  documented Claude Code env-injection mechanism â€” append with `>>` so other hooks' vars\n  survive). Uses `python3` (already a rebar dependency) to parse the JSON robustly. Exits 0\n  and never blocks the session (fire-and-forget); a missing/blank `session_id` or absent\n  `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` is a silent no-op. Idempotent: re-firing on resume/clear/compact simply\n  re-exports the same value (last export wins).\n- **Docs (`docs/session-id-shims.md`).** A new install guide: the `settings.json`\n  `hooks.SessionStart` snippet pointing at the script, the caveat that the id is NOT stable\n  across `--resume`/`--continue`/fork/subagents (epic gotcha G1 â€” treat it as \"the session\n  that emitted the claim event\"), and guidance to keep it session-scoped (do NOT export\n  `REBAR_SESSION_ID` from a shell profile â€” gotcha G3). Cross-links `docs/config.md`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the Claude Code SessionStart hook script, the install docs page, and a unit test that\n  validates the script (valid shell + correct env-file output given a mock stdin).\n- OUT: Codex/Cursor shims (S6 / 7656, which extend the same docs page); the record/read core\n  (S1-S3, S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` exists and is valid shell. Proof:\n      `bash -n scripts/session-shims/claude-code-session-start.sh` (asserted in\n      `tests/unit/test_session_shims.py`).\n- [ ] Given stdin `{\"session_id\":\"abc123\"}` and a `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE` temp path, the script\n      writes `export REBAR_SESSION_ID=abc123` AND `export AI_AGENT=claude-code` to that file.\n      Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k claude_code -q` runs the script and\n      asserts both lines.\n- [ ] A blank/missing `session_id` (or unset `CLAUDE_ENV_FILE`) is a no-op with exit 0 (never\n      blocks the session). Proof: `pytest tests/unit/test_session_shims.py -k claude_code_noop -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/session-id-shims.md` documents the `settings.json` install snippet, the G1\n      id-instability caveat, and the session-scoped (not-in-profile) guidance. Proof: a\n      doc-content assert in `test_session_shims.py`.\n\n## Depends on\n- S1 (the `REBAR_SESSION_ID` contract) and S5 (the `AI_AGENT` -> `claim_harness` contract)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783546962814643001,"uuid":"9a4c30d1-aed2-4e8d-80d6-584f89301c3c"}